<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="ie=edge">
    <title>Jobs</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="indeed.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="one">
    <h1 class="text2">Search  and apply for the Web-Developer<br> position that you're looking for... </h1>
    
     <h3 class="text">If you are planning to start a career as a Web Developer take a look at all the possibilities that you could have ones you are ready to get a job and which abilities the companies are looking for the most. And if you already have some knowledge you might find some entry label job. 
        </h3>
   
    </div>

    <div class="two">

    <form action="/" method="POST" >
        <input name="work" class="input" type="text" placeholder="Enter job"  style="font-size: 20px;">
        <input onclick="scrollWin(0, 300)" class="buttom" type="submit" value="Find"  style="font-size: 20px;" >
    </form>

 <% if(job !== null){ %>

    <% for(let i=0; i< job.length; i++) { %>
       <br><br><br><br><br> <h2 class="h2"><%= job[i].title %></h1>
        <h2><%= job[i].company.name %></h2>
        <h3><%= job[i].company.url %></h3>
       <% if(job[i].company.location){ %>
          <h3><%= job[i].company.location.name %></h3>
       <%} %>
        <a href="<%= job[i].apply_url%>" target="_blank" id="apply">Apply Now</a>
    <% } %>
<% }%>

</div>

<script>
    function scrollWin(x, y) {
      window.scrollBy(x, y);
    }
    </script>

</body>
</html>